        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks AG for the first part of his "Statistics [of the flora of the northern U. S.", <hi rend="italic">Am. J. Sci.</hi> 2d ser. 22 (1856): 204–32; 2d ser. 23 (1857): 62–84, 369–403]</p> 
            <p>and for information on social and varying plants.</p>
            <p>Would like to know number of genera of introduced plants in U. S.</p>
            <p>Is surprised at some affinities of northern U. S. flora and asks for any climatic explanations.</p>
            <p>Asks what proportion of genera common to U. S. and Europe are mundane.</p>
            <p>Is glad AG will work out the northern ranges of the European species and the ranges of species with regard to size of genera.</p>
        </abstract>
